author: ff m
message:
✨ 安装脚本支持安装到指定目录，支持选择desktop创建至 $HOME/.local/share/applications/ or $HOME/Desktop
The most significant changes to the `online_install.sh` script involve the addition of user prompts for customization of the installation path and the location of the desktop file. The script now includes a loop to allow the user to input a custom installation path or use the default one. If the user provides an invalid path, they are prompted to input again. The script also creates the installation path and switches to it, outputting an error message and exiting with status 1 if it fails to do so. A new function, `InitDesktop`, has been added to prompt the user to choose where to add the desktop file. The user can choose between `$HOME/.local/share/applications/` and `$HOME/Desktop`. The script then removes any existing desktop file in the chosen location and creates a new one. If the user provides an invalid option, they are prompted to input again.

List of changes:

1. A loop has been added to prompt the user to input a custom installation path or use the default path. If the user provides an invalid path, they are prompted to input again (online_install.sh).

2. The script now creates the installation path and switches to it. If it fails to do either, it outputs an error message and exits with status 1 (online_install.sh).

3. A function `InitDesktop` has been added to prompt the user to choose where to add the desktop file. The user can choose between `$HOME/.local/share/applications/` and `$HOME/Desktop`. The script then removes any existing desktop file in the chosen location and creates a new one. If the user provides an invalid option, they are prompted to input again (online_install.sh).

4. The function `InitDesktop` is called to execute the above changes (online_install.sh).

message:
🐛 The most significant changes include the update of the `ItemsPerLine` property in `CarouselItems.axaml` to use a binding to the parent `spp:CarouselItems`'s `ItemsPerPage` property, the replacement of a large block of code in `HomePage.axaml` with a new block that sets up a `spp:CarouselItems` control with a custom `ItemTemplate`, and the addition of a new line of code in `GameAcceleratorService.cs` to update the `LastAccelerateTime` property of the `app` object.

Here is a list of the changes:

1. In `CarouselItems.axaml`, the `ItemsPerLine` property of `spp:FixedWrapPanel` has been updated to use a binding to the parent `spp:CarouselItems`'s `ItemsPerPage` property. This change allows the number of items per line to dynamically adjust based on the parent's `ItemsPerPage` property.

2. In `HomePage.axaml`, a large block of code related to an `ItemsControl` has been commented out and replaced with a new block of code that sets up a `spp:CarouselItems` control with a custom `ItemTemplate`. This change simplifies the code and makes it easier to manage the items in the carousel.

3. In `GameAcceleratorService.cs`, a new line of code has been added to update the `LastAccelerateTime` property of the `app` object to the current time when the `startCode` is `101`. This change ensures that the `LastAccelerateTime` property is always up-to-date.

4. In `GameInfoPageViewModel.cs`, two new lines of code have been added to set the `SelectedArea` and `SelectedServer` properties of `XunYouGame` to `null` in the `BackSelectArea` method. This change resets the selected area and server when the user goes back to the select area page.

5. In `GameAppItem.axaml`, several changes have been made to the styles and properties of various elements. These changes improve the appearance of the game app item.

6. In `AcceleratorPage2.axaml.cs`, the `SearchGameBox_SelectionChanged` event handler has been replaced with a `SearchGameBox_DropDownClosed` event handler. This change improves the user experience by resetting the search box and scrolling the game list to the top after a game is selected.

author: RMBGAME
message:
🐛 The most significant changes involve modifications to the `GameAcceleratorService` and the layout of the game accelerator page. In `GameAcceleratorService`, the `RestoreGameStatus` method now sets `PingValue` to a new default value, and the logic for adding and updating games has been altered. The condition for early return in the game area selection method has also been changed. The layout of the game accelerator page has been restructured, with changes to the placement of `ScrollViewer` and `GameDetail` component.

1. The default value for `PingValue` in `XunYouGameViewModel` has been changed from an empty string to a constant string `DefaultPingValue` set to `"--"`.
2. `RestoreGameStatus` method in `GameAcceleratorService` now sets `PingValue` to `DefaultPingValue` instead of `"0"`.
3. The logic for adding and updating games in `GameAcceleratorService` has been modified. If the game is found in `MyGames`, it is now removed before being added again.
4. The condition for early return in the game area selection method in `GameAcceleratorService` now checks if `SelectedArea` is null on `vm.XunYouGame` instead of `app`.
5. The layout of the game accelerator page in `AcceleratorPage2.axaml` has been changed. The `ScrollViewer` has been moved inside the `ContentLoader` and the `GameDetail` component has been moved outside the `ScrollViewer`.
6. The `ItemsRepeater` in `GameListPage.axaml` now has a `VerticalCacheLength` of `300`.

author: RMBGAME
message:
🐛 The most significant changes involve the `GameAcceleratorService` class and the `GameAppItem.axaml` and `GameDetail.axaml` files. In the `GameAcceleratorService` class, the variable `game2` is now used instead of `game` in certain cases, and the properties `IsAccelerated`, `IsAccelerating`, and `LastAccelerateTime` are now set directly on `game2`. The class also now includes `SelectedArea` and `SelectedServer` in the `GameInfoPageViewModel` instance creation and uses an async version of `GameAccelerator`. In the `GameAppItem.axaml` and `GameDetail.axaml` files, new styles and properties have been added and some properties have been moved or removed.

Changes:

1. The `GameAcceleratorService` class now uses `game2` instead of `game` in the switch case for `XunYouState.加速中` and `XunYouState.加速已完成`. The properties `IsAccelerated`, `IsAccelerating`, and `LastAccelerateTime` are now set directly on `game2` (Code Change 1).
2. The `GameAcceleratorService` class now includes `SelectedArea` and `SelectedServer` in the `GameInfoPageViewModel` instance creation (Code Change 2).
3. The `GameAcceleratorService` class now uses an async version of `GameAccelerator` (Code Change 3).
4. The `GameInfoPageViewModel` class has been updated to change the second parameter of `WhenPropertyChanged` from `false` to `true` for `XunYouGame.SelectedArea` (Code Change 4).
5. The `GameAppItem.axaml` file has been updated with a new style for `Grid Panel.AppName TextBlock.LeftMargin` and new properties for `spp:Image2`. The `Margin` property of `TextBlock` has been moved to a new class `Classes.LeftMargin` (Code Change 5).
6. The `GameDetail.axaml` file has been updated to move the `spp:Image2` inside a `StackPanel` and add `IsVisible` and `Margin` properties to it. The `Margin` property of `TextBlock` has been removed (Code Change 6).
7. The `AcceleratorPage2.axaml.cs` file has been updated to add a new dictionary `dictPinYinArray` and a new method `GameContains` that checks if a game contains a given text using case-insensitive comparison and Pinyin comparison. The `TextSelector` and `TextFilter` properties of `SearchGameBox` have been set to `null` and `GameContains` respectively (Code Change 7).

author: RMBGAME
message:
🐛 The most significant changes are in the `AuthenticatorHomePageViewModel.cs` and `AuthenticatorHomePage.axaml` files. In the ViewModel, a new else block has been added to set `IsVerificationPass` to true when the condition for the if statement is not met. In the axaml file, the visibility of the `StackPanel` is now directly bound to the `IsVerificationPass` property, simplifying the visibility condition. The `MultiBinding` converter code has been commented out, indicating it is no longer in use.

List of changes:

1. A new else block has been added to the `AuthenticatorHomePageViewModel.cs` file. This block sets `IsVerificationPass` to true when the if statement's condition is not met.

2. In the `AuthenticatorHomePage.axaml` file, the visibility of the `StackPanel` is now directly bound to the `IsVerificationPass` property. This change simplifies the visibility condition of the `StackPanel`.

3. The `MultiBinding` converter code, which was previously used to bind `IsVerificationPass` and `Auths.Count` to the visibility of the `StackPanel`, has been commented out. This indicates that it is no longer in use but is kept for possible future reference.

4. No changes have been made to the `TextBlock` element. It is included for context.

author: RMBGAME
message:
🐛 The most significant changes involve the `GameAccelerator` method in the `GameAcceleratorService` class and the `GameAcceleratorCommand` ReactiveCommand. The `GameAccelerator` method has been changed from an asynchronous void method to an asynchronous Task method, allowing for improved error handling and control flow. The `GameAcceleratorCommand` has been updated to reflect this change. Additionally, a new property `IsAccelerating` has been added to the `XunYouGameViewModel` class to better track the state of the game acceleration process.

Changes:

1. The `GameAccelerator` method in the `GameAcceleratorService` class has been changed from an asynchronous void method to an asynchronous Task method. This change allows for better error handling and control flow.

2. The `GameAcceleratorCommand` ReactiveCommand has been updated to use `CreateFromTask` instead of `Create`, reflecting the change in the `GameAccelerator` method.

3. A new property `IsAccelerating` has been added to the `XunYouGameViewModel` class. This property is set to `true` at the start of the `GameAccelerator` method and is set to `false` in various places where the method may return early due to an error or condition not being met. This change allows for better tracking of the state of the game acceleration process.

4. The line setting `app.IsAccelerating` to `true` has been removed from the end of the `GameAccelerator` method, as it is now set at the start of the method.

5. In the case where the game acceleration is stopped successfully, the line setting `app.IsAccelerating` to `true` has been removed. In the case where stopping the game acceleration fails, `app.IsAccelerating` is now set to `false`.

author: RMBGAME
message:
🐛 The most significant changes involve the `GameAcceleratorService.cs` file, where new cases have been added to the switch statement to handle different states of the game accelerator. The `SetGameStatus` method has also been updated to check and update the `CurrentAcceleratorGame` properties. In addition, changes have been made to the `GameDetail.axaml`, `AcceleratorPage2.axaml`, `AcceleratorPage2.axaml.cs`, and `MainFramePage.axaml` files to modify UI elements and functionality.

1. `GameAcceleratorService.cs` has been updated to include a new case for `XunYouState.加速中` in the switch statement. This case checks if the `GameId` is not 0 and `CurrentAcceleratorGame` is null, then it creates a new `XunYouGameViewModel` instance and assigns it to `CurrentAcceleratorGame`.
2. A new case for `XunYouState.加速已断开` has been added to the switch statement in `GameAcceleratorService.cs`. This case stops the speed test and updates the game status.
3. The `SetGameStatus` method in `GameAcceleratorService.cs` has been updated to check if `CurrentAcceleratorGame` is not null and its `Id` is equal to `game.Id`. If true, it updates the `CurrentAcceleratorGame` properties. If `SelectedArea` is null, it fetches the game info and updates `SelectedArea` and `SelectedServer`.
4. The `GameDetail.axaml` file has been updated to change the `Foreground` color of two `TextBlock` elements.
5. The `AcceleratorPage2.axaml` file has been updated to remove some UI elements related to the Watt Accelerator installation path and add them back later in the file. The order of some elements has been changed.
6. The `AcceleratorPage2.axaml.cs` file has been updated to clear the selected item in `SearchGameBox` after adding a game to `GameAcceleratorService`.
7. The `MainFramePage.axaml` file has been updated to comment out a `TabStripItem` related to the community fix.
